f expertise in institutional investment and fiduciary work francis x lilly area chairman of gfa in washington dc noted that davies brings a complementary skill set that makes him a natural fit for gfa nick has extensive experience from the us and uk on pension investment issues including liabilitydriven investing strategies pension risk transfer and alternative investments across private and public markets lilly said gfa has a strong history of providing investment advisory and independent fiduciary services and both are essential to financial management decisions for defined benefit plan sponsors as well as k veba and other clients nick brings extensive knowledge about the value of broader consulting across the benefits landscape and im confident that our investment advisory and fiduciary decisionmaking businesses will continue to grow under his leadership said david ziegler executive vice president of gallagher benefit services davies joins a highly qualified gfa team as one of three chartered alternative investment analysts client interests are also served by  investment professionals who are chartered financial analysts four attorneys with erisa experience and one certified public accountant about gallagher benefit services gallagher benefit services inc a subsidiary of arthur j gallagher  co nyse ajg is one of the leading employee benefits brokers and consultants in the us it delivers a full range of employee benefits services including benefits strategy plan design and management financial planning actuarial data analysis and benchmarking retirement brokerage and consulting and human resource services to learn more visit wwwgallagherbenefitscom about gallagher fiduciary advisors gallagher fiduciary advisors llc gfa is an institutional investment and fiduciary advisory firm of  employees with primary offices in washington dc newark nj and pittsburgh pa gfa delivers independent conflictfree investment advisory and fiduciary services that include investment advis